        <h3>16.3 Washington State (My Health My Data Act)</h3>
        <p>If you are a Washington consumer, the following additional rights and protections apply to "Consumer Health Data" under MHMDA:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>What counts as Consumer Health Data:</strong> under MHMDA the term is <strong>very broad</strong>. It includes everything we list as "health data" in Section 3 plus inferences that could be drawn from non-health data. Treat every category in Section 3 marked "health data" or "derived health data" as Consumer Health Data, and assume MHMDA also covers inferences we draw from any combination of your data.</li>
          <li><strong>Sources:</strong> directly from you; from your device.</li>
          <li><strong>Categories with whom we share:</strong> the sub-processors in Section 7.1; and, <strong>only with your explicit and separate authorization</strong>, the commercial buyers under our Tier 2 and Tier 3 programs.</li>
          <li><strong>No sale without a valid authorization.</strong> We do not "sell" Consumer Health Data without a separate, signed, and dated authorization that names the buyer and is valid for no more than one year. The authorization is requested, captured, and stored on a dedicated screen — it is not bundled into the Privacy Notice, the Terms of Service, or the general consent gate.</li>
          <li><strong>MHMDA rights</strong> — access (a list of third parties to whom we have shared your Consumer Health Data), confirmation, withdrawal of consent and authorization, and <strong>deletion (which cascades to all our records and to our sub-processors)</strong>. Use <strong>Settings → Privacy → My Health My Data rights</strong>.</li>
          <li><strong>No discrimination</strong> for exercising MHMDA rights.</li>
          <li><strong>Private right of action</strong> — MHMDA provides a private right of action for violations. You can also complain to the Washington State Attorney General at <a href="https://www.atg.wa.gov" rel="noopener">atg.wa.gov</a>.</li>
        </ul>

